@startuml
title Agri Watch - RAG Question Answering Sequence

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #3F4E5E
  LifeLineBorderColor #3F4E5E
  ParticipantBorderColor #3F4E5E
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #F7F9FC
}

actor User
participant "FastAPI API" as API
participant "LocalRAG" as RAG
participant "HashingEmbedder" as Embedder
database "SQLiteStore" as Store
participant "Similarity Search" as Search
participant "PromptBuilder" as Prompt
participant "LLMClient" as Client
participant "Local Llama Model" as LLM

User -> API : POST /rag/ask\nquery and top_k
activate API

API -> RAG : answer(query, top_k)
activate RAG

RAG -> RAG : Infer optional category filters
RAG -> Embedder : embed(query)
Embedder --> RAG : query vector

RAG -> Store : list_chunks()
Store --> RAG : chunks, article metadata,\nand stored vectors

RAG -> Search : cosine similarity\nand category filtering
Search --> RAG : ranked top-k matches

alt No relevant matches
  RAG --> API : No-information answer\nempty matches and sources
else Relevant matches found
  RAG -> Prompt : Build context from matches
  Prompt --> RAG : grounded messages or prompt

  RAG -> Client : answer_from_context(query, context)
  activate Client

  Client -> LLM : create_chat_completion()
  activate LLM
  LLM --> Client : generated answer
  deactivate LLM

  Client --> RAG : answer text
  deactivate Client

  RAG -> RAG : Build unique source list
  RAG --> API : answer, matches and sources
end

deactivate RAG
API --> User : JSON response
deactivate API

note over RAG,LLM
This diagram assumes the corrected flow:
category filters affect retrieval, but do not
bypass local LLM generation when matches exist.
end note

@enduml
